Generation AI's <strong>Teachable Machine</strong> has been adopted as part of Microsoft's <strong>FarmBeats for Students</strong> STEM package. The Microsoft Learn module <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/modules/introduce-ai-data-science-stem-farmbeats-students/">Introduce AI and data science in STEM education with FarmBeats for Students</a> is a <strong>10-unit</strong>, <strong>beginner-level</strong> module designed for <strong>K-12 educators</strong>.
{% endset %}
{% include "blocks/kadence/advancedheading.njk" %}

<p>According to the module description, the package engages learners with AI, data science, precision agriculture, and sustainability through hands-on STEM activities. The page lists <strong>Excel</strong>, <strong>Microsoft MakeCode</strong>, and <strong>Microsoft 365 Education</strong> as the main tools and platforms.</p>

<p>This is an important milestone for the project because Teachable Machine now appears in Microsoft's international learning environment as part of a broader STEM education package. The page HTML includes the metadata value <code>ms.date = 2025-04-28T00:00:00Z</code>, and this entry is dated accordingly.</p>
